            <div class="projekt-1-text">
                <h2>
                    FANTASTICUS
                </h2>
                <h4>
                    Baroque Fantasy<br>     
                    Without Borders
                </h4>
                <p class="projekt-text-p">
                    Virtuosity, madness, and a sonic journey through the 17th-century Habsburg Empire. Fantasticus is a program brimming with intense, virtuosic challenges in stylus fantasticus—a style full of musical ecstasy, unfettered improvisation, and unexpected twists. It is a collision of well-known sonatas by H.I.F. Biber with nearly forgotten compositions, such as the recently rediscovered Sonata in D minor by Heinricus Litzkau, a true musical gem.   
                    Recorded by Da Vinci Publishing, this project is a journey into the world of Baroque fantasy, where everything is possible, and the boundaries between compositions, emotions, and imagination blur, creating a single, cohesive, pulsating work.
                </p>
